BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mooch the Magnificent
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260421T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260421T213000
UID:ai1ec-148418-94937@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Bridges MAYO\, Reimagining Opera for Kids\, and Stages Bloomin
 gton have teamed up to produce Lauren Bernofsky’s “Mooch the Magnifice
 nt\,” with stage director Andrew Keeler and musical director Dr. Lauren 
 Bernofsky. Youth singers and instrumentalists\, ages 8-18\, have been rehe
 arsing alongside professional Reimagining Opera for Kids opera singers\, I
 U Jacobs and community musicians to share a tale about a zookeeper\, Orlan
 do\, and his assistant\, Mooch. Scored for full orchestra and singers\, se
 e what happens when Mooch helps the mechanical animals to disconnect on Tu
 esday\, April 21 at 7:30PM at Fairview Elementary School gym!“When the c
 leverest person in the room is … the girl. MOOCH THE MAGNIFICENT is a 40
 -minute opera on a libretto by Scott Russell Sanders. The setting is a zoo
  of the future\, populated not by animals but by robots in animal form. Mo
 och\, an orphan girl\, convinces the zookeeper to hire her to fix the robo
 ts when they break down\, but she secretly reprograms them to be increasin
 gly wild.”
LOCATION:Fairview Elementary 500 W 7th St\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/mooch-the-magnificent/?instance_id=94937
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
