BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Green Drinks Bloomington: Common Wealth: Living in a Shared World.
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260422T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260422T193000
UID:ai1ec-148338-94903@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Green Drinks Bloomington is a lively\, informal social network
 ing event for people from all walks of life who are interested in making a
  greener world. Green Drinks gathers monthly to share libations and dialog
 ue\, explore ideas and make new friends and business connections.On Earth 
 Day\, Wednesday\, April 22 at 6 PM (doors open at 5:30)\, Green Drinks Blo
 omington will offer a presentation by Scott Russell Sanders\, Distinguishe
 d Professor Emeritus of English at Indiana University\, and a fellow of th
 e American Academy of Arts and Sciences. He will speak about “Common Wea
 lth: Living in a Shared World.” Our wellbeing depends far more on the we
 alth we share than our private finances and possessions. This talk will ce
 lebrate the gifts of nature and culture that support and enrich our lives.
  It will also show how these shared riches—atmosphere\, oceans\, biodive
 rsity\, parks and public schools\, arts and science\, laws and language\, 
 and many more—are under assault by those who wish to exploit them for pe
 rsonal or corporate gain. By recognizing the common wealth that sustains u
 s\, we may be moved to defend it.Green Drinks Bloomington is held the 4th 
 Wednesday of the month through October from 5:30 – 7:30 pm at the Upland
  Brewing Company’s Wood Shop venue. Some food will be provided. To recei
 ve a monthly reminder\, write[email protected]. To learn more about Green
  Drinks visit www.greendrinks.org.
LOCATION:Upland Brewing Co. Wood Shop: 350 w. 11th st.
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/green-drinks-bloomington-common-wealth-living-i
 n-a-shared-world/?instance_id=94903
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
