BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Author event with David George
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260424T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260424T190000
UID:ai1ec-148028-94729@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:We invite you to join us for an evening with biologist and aut
 hor David George Haskell in celebration of his new book\,How Flowers Made 
 Our World: The Story of Nature’s Revolutionaries!For this event\, David 
 will be in conversation with IU biology professor Jen Lau.Hosted in coordi
 nation with IU’sEnvironmental Futures in the Arts and Humanities initiat
 ive.ABOUT THE BOOK:An exquisite exploration of the power of flowers\, plac
 ing them at the center of the story of how evolution created the world we 
 know today.Looking to the future\, flowers offer us lessons on resilience 
 and creativity in the face of rapid environmental change. We need floral c
 reativity\, beauty\, and joy more than ever.How Flowers Made Our Worldcomb
 ines lyrical writing\, sensual exploration\, and the latest in scientific 
 research to explore some of the most consequential life forms ever to have
  evolved\, showing how our planet came to be and how it thrives today.
LOCATION:Morgenstern Books & Cafe\, 849 South Auto Mall Drive\, Bloomingto
 n
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/author-event-with-david-george/?instance_id=947
 29
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
