SUMMARY:Shrek The Musical\, JR
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260424T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260424T210000
UID:ai1ec-148348-94911@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Once upon a time\, in a far away swamp\, there lived an ogre n
 amed Shrek.  One day\, Shrek finds his swamp invaded by banished fairyta
 le misfits who have been cast off by Lord Farquaad\, a tiny terror with bi
 g ambitions. When Shrek sets off with a wisecracking donkey to confront Fa
 rquaad\, he’s handed a task — if he rescues feisty princess Fiona\, hi
 s swamp will be righted. Shrek tries to win Fiona’s love and vanquish Lo
 rd Farquaad\, but a fairytale wouldn’t be complete without a few twists 
 and turns along the way.Part romance and part twisted fairy tale\, Shrek 
 JR. is an irreverently fun show with a powerful message for the whole fami
 ly.April 24\, 7:00 pmApril 25\, 2:00 pm & 7:00 pmApril 26\, noonDirected b
 y Annalise CainMusic Direction By Ben HandelChoreography by Jada BuehlerSt
 age Management by Kyli Gott-JacobsSet Design by Brian LewisCostume Design 
 by Becky UnderwoodProps Design by Leah TannenAssistant Direction by Liz Hi
 ggsProduction Assistance by Leah Rodkin
LOCATION:The Warehouse Bloomington: 1525 S. Rogers St.
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/shrek-the-musical-jr/?instance_id=94911
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:John Primer & the Real Deal Blues Band\, with special guests Paul 
 Holdman and Gordon Bonham.
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260424T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260424T213000
UID:ai1ec-148613-95028@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:As a young man\, guitarist\, vocalist\, and bandleader John Pr
 imer learned Chicago blues with the masters. Primer performed regularly wi
 th legends such as Muddy Waters\, Willie Dixon\, and was a long-term band 
 leader for Magic Slim & The Teardrops. Primer is one of the few truly-auth
 entic Chicago bluesmen touring and recording today. He was inducted into t
 he Blues Hall of Fame in 2023.Primer’s long list of honors and accolades
  speak to his experience and reputation for engaging a live audience\, inc
 luding: Three-time Grammy® Award nominee\; Blues Artist of the Year — L
 iving Blues critic’s poll award\; Traditional Blues Artist of the Year 
 — Blues Music Award\; Lifetime Achievement Award\, Live Album of the Yea
 r\, and Traditional Blues Album of the Year — Blues Blast Awards
LOCATION:Brown County Playhouse\, 70 S. Van Buren St\, Nashville
